---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement - JSON Formatter Pro"
  description="JSON Formatter Pro is committed to accessibility. Learn about our WCAG 2.2 AA compliance and accessibility features."
  path="/accessibility"
  keywords="accessibility, WCAG, ADA, inclusive design"
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 text-sm text-subtle">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-fg">Accessibility Statement</h1>

    <p class="mt-4 text-base text-fg font-semibold">
      JSON Formatter Pro is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for
      people with disabilities.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">
      Commitment to Accessibility
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We are committed to providing an accessible web experience for all users,
      regardless of their abilities. We continuously work to improve the
      accessibility of JSON Formatter Pro to conform to <strong
        >WCAG 2.2 Level AA</strong
      > standards.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Accessibility Features</h2>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold text-fg">🎹 Keyboard Navigation</h3>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Full keyboard navigation throughout the entire application</li>
      <li>Logical tab order for all interactive elements</li>
      <li>Skip-to-editor link to bypass repetitive elements</li>
      <li>Keyboard shortcuts available via command palette (Ctrl/Cmd + K)</li>
      <li>All functionality accessible without a mouse</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold text-fg">👁️ Vision</h3>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>
        <strong>High Contrast Themes:</strong> Light and dark modes with sufficient
        color contrast (WCAG AA compliant)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Color Contrast:</strong> Text-to-background contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1
        for normal text
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Focus Indicators:</strong> Visible focus rings on all interactive
        elements
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Resizable Text:</strong> Text can be resized without loss of functionality
        (up to 200%)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>No Flashing:</strong> No content flashes more than 3 times per second
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold text-fg">
      🔊 Screen Reader Support
    </h3>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Semantic HTML markup for proper structure</li>
      <li>ARIA labels and descriptions for interactive elements</li>
      <li>ARIA live regions for status updates and error messages</li>
      <li>Proper heading hierarchy (H1, H2, H3, etc.)</li>
      <li>Alternative text for all icons and images</li>
      <li>Form labels associated with inputs</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold text-fg">🎬 Motion & Animation</h3>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>
        <strong>Respects `prefers-reduced-motion`:</strong> Animations are disabled
        for users who prefer reduced motion
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>No Auto-Play:</strong> No automatically playing audio or video content
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Minimal Animation:</strong> Subtle transitions that don't distract
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold text-fg">📱 Responsive Design</h3>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Fully responsive on mobile, tablet, and desktop devices</li>
      <li>Touch targets at least 44×44 CSS pixels</li>
      <li>Readable on all device sizes without horizontal scrolling</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold text-fg">🌐 Additional Support</h3>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Clear and simple language throughout</li>
      <li>Consistent navigation and layout</li>
      <li>Error messages with clear, actionable suggestions</li>
      <li>No time limits for interaction with the tool</li>
      <li>Works with browser zoom and text resizing</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Accessibility Testing</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      JSON Formatter Pro is regularly tested for accessibility compliance using:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Automated accessibility scanners (axe, WAVE)</li>
      <li>Manual keyboard navigation testing</li>
      <li>Screen reader testing (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)</li>
      <li>Color contrast verification</li>
      <li>WCAG 2.2 compliance audits</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Known Limitations</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      While we strive for full accessibility, some areas may have limitations:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>
        The JSON editor (CodeMirror) may have complex keyboard interactions for
        advanced users
      </li>
      <li>
        Very large JSON files (50+ MB) may have performance impacts on some
        devices
      </li>
      <li>
        Some color combinations in exported code blocks may not meet perfect
        contrast ratios
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">
      Assistive Technology Compatibility
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-2">JSON Formatter Pro is tested and compatible with:</p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>
        <strong>Screen Readers:</strong> NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver (Mac/iOS), Narrator
        (Windows), TalkBack (Android)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Browser Extensions:</strong> Password managers, ad blockers, accessibility
        extensions
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>OS Features:</strong> Windows High Contrast Mode, macOS accessibility
        features, mobile accessibility features
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Standards & Guidelines</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">JSON Formatter Pro aims to comply with:</p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>
        <strong>WCAG 2.2 Level AA:</strong> Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.2
      </li>
      <li><strong>ADA:</strong> Americans with Disabilities Act</li>
      <li>
        <strong>AODA:</strong> Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act
      </li>
      <li><strong>EN 301 549:</strong> European accessibility standard</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">
      Feedback & Accessibility Issues
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We welcome accessibility feedback. If you encounter any accessibility
      barriers while using JSON Formatter Pro, please:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>
        Email us at <a
          href="mailto:hashcode.dev@gmail.com"
          class="text-primary hover:underline">hashcode.dev@gmail.com</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/contact" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contact us</a> with
        details about the issue
      </li>
      <li>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/hashcode-dev/json-formatter-pro/issues"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-primary hover:underline">Open a GitHub issue</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-3">Please include:</p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Description of the accessibility barrier</li>
      <li>The browser and assistive technology you're using</li>
      <li>Steps to reproduce the issue</li>
      <li>How the issue impacts your ability to use the tool</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Third-Party Content</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      JSON Formatter Pro may include third-party content (e.g., ads) that we
      don't control. We make reasonable efforts to ensure third-party content is
      also accessible, but we recommend reporting any accessibility issues with
      ads or external content.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Continuous Improvement</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Accessibility is an ongoing commitment. We continuously work to:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Improve accessibility of existing features</li>
      <li>Test new features for accessibility before release</li>
      <li>Stay updated with WCAG guidelines and best practices</li>
      <li>Incorporate user feedback on accessibility</li>
      <li>Train our team on accessibility best practices</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Last Updated</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      This Accessibility Statement was last updated in July 2026. We review and
      update this statement regularly.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
